In view of the resistance in Europe, three possible ways out of the crisis are started in Germany.
The first is a strong euro with Germany, Austria, the Netherlands and other countries, while the South should leave the euro area.
The second: The reintroduction of the German mark - even though it now sounds more like science fiction -, supported by a large majority of public opinion, about 50 percent of the population.
The third: a redesign of the euro according to German proposals. This means: more macroeconomic control; strict financial management; punishment of countries that exceed the targets; possibly the payment of some countries and the extension of the costs of potential adjustment to the private sector.
