The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
Before their conversation with the consulate, the persons must introduce themselves to the services for the visa application; the costs will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will change in the United States Embassy and in the consulates.
In the new procedure, most of the applicants will have to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) before their conversation at the consulate.
The ASC staff shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be checked by the consulate before the interview.
The new process has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total costs for the handling of the visa are falling, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the time-limit, the processing of the visa application and the transport service that the document is handed over to.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the current rate of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for traders and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa need not have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to imagine at the next ASC where they submit their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the conversation in the consulate will remain there less time than before.
Those who request the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service fee of 26 dollars.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, see: http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
